I reviewed the telemetry and followed the prescribed diagnosis workflow. Key observations: a strong orders latency-90 spike (~2.66×P95) beginning at ~2024-01-20T00:35:00Z, concurrent elevated socket metrics across many services at the same time (consistent with a network/socket event), and co-temporal RabbitMQ disk I/O and queue-master memory spikes that could be contributing infrastructure events. Given the allowed candidate components and the metric severity/timing, the most likely root cause is the orders service experiencing a network/socket-related degradation.

